DESCRIPTION:<p>Cranksgiving is a fun choose-your-own-adventure event all ab
 out riding a bike and giving back to our communities in need during the hol
 iday season. <b>This year’s beneficiary is Healing Transitions.</b></p><p>W
 e’ll provide you with a list of essential food items to purchase\, offer so
 me challenges for bonus points\, and give you a map of nearby grocery store
 s. However\, how you choose to participate is entirely up to you! Whether y
 ou ride to just one store or visit them all\, join as a team or go solo\, w
 e’re happy to see you on your bike doing some good!</p><p>We will be giving
  out points for weight\, distance\, and key items. So grab your cargo bike\
 , panniers\, backpack\, and any and everything you can mount to your bike t
 o carry a load. </p><p>Learn more about Cranksgiving: <a href="https://cran
 ksgiving.org/" target="_blank">https://cranksgiving.org/</a></p><p>Learn mo
 re about Healing Transitions: <a href="https://healing-transitions.org/" ta
 rget="_blank">https://healing-transitions.org/</a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20241111T152039Z
LOCATION:Crank Arm Brewing Company\, 319 W Davie St\, Raleigh\, NC 27601\, 
 USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Cranksgiving: A Bicycle Food Drive for Healing Transitions
TRANSP:OPAQUE
