CREATED:20250403T154536Z
DESCRIPTION:Raleigh Community Kickstand is offering a series of free bike r
 epair workshops. These workshops are intended for folks of all skill levels
 \, whether you want to learn how to maintain your own bike or volunteer wit
 h us in the future to tune up a bike for folks in the community. All are we
 lcome!\n\nYou can come to either or both of the sessions. On May 6th\, we w
 ill cover basic bike maintenance including flat fixing\, chain maintenance\
 , brake adjustments\, and more. On May 27th\, we will cover drivetrain main
 tenance\, including derailleur adjustments and shifting overhauls. Bring yo
 ur own bike or learn using one of ours. Come ready to get your hands a bit 
 greasy and throw back a Raleigh Brewing Company beer\, cider\, kombucha\, o
 r seltzer!
LAST-MODIFIED:20250409T151449Z
LOCATION:Raleigh Brewing Company\, 3709 Neil St\, Raleigh\, NC 27607\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Free Bike Repair Workshop: Basic Bike Maintenance
TRANSP:OPAQUE
