CREATED:20250627T221835Z
DESCRIPTION:Raleigh Community Kickstand is offering a basic bike maintenanc
 e workshop where you'll learn the skills you need to feel safe and self-suf
 ficient on your bike. We'll cover the essentials of bike maintenance like: 
 fixing flats\, chain care\, brake and shifting adjustments\, and more. We'l
 l also share resources on bike repair\, local infrastructure and organizati
 ons\, and how to navigate the world via bike.<br><br>Bring your bike if you
  can. No experience required. Sign up to let us know you’re coming.<br><br>
 Sign-up: <a href="https://raleighcommunitykickstand.org/workshop" target="_
 blank">raleighcommunitykickstand.org/workshop</a><br>When: Monday\, July 7 
 6-8pm<br>Where: RUMAH (415 Hillsborough St)<br>Suggested donation: $5 (no o
 ne turned away for lack of funds). Of the collected donations\, $50 will be
  donated to RUMAH for use of the space. Any additional proceeds will suppor
 t Raleigh Community Kickstand's efforts to provide free bike repair for all
 .
LAST-MODIFIED:20250628T131845Z
LOCATION:RUMAH\, 415 Hillsborough St Suite 101\, Raleigh\, NC 27603\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Basic Bike Maintenance Workshop @ RUMAH
